@Node "--background--" "msql.library/--background--"

@{b}    The msql.library is an Amiga shared library that grant access to a mSQL@{ub}
@{b}    database engine over a TCP/IP network (ie include the mSQL client part).@{ub}

@{b}    @{"MsqlNumRows()" Link "MsqlNumRows()"} & @{"MsqlNumFields()" Link "MsqlNumFields()"} are macros #defined in libraries/msql.h@{ub}
@{b}    Please refer to the original documentation for more information.@{ub}

@{b}   News from Version 5.3:@{ub}
       - Include 2.0.7 code changes.

@{b}   News from Version 5.2:@{ub}
       - Fix a bug that make @{"MsqlUnixTimeToDate" Link "msql.guide/MsqlUnixTimeToDate"} unusable.
       - Some code changes and bugs fix from the original
         API (V2.0.5 & 2.0.6)

@{b}   News from Version 5:@{ub}
       - Some ARexx host bugs removed.
       - ARexx allocation trace (Free all ARexx allocation with one
         function).
       - Add a hook monitoring system.

@{b}   News from Version 4:@{ub}
       - ARexx host.

@{b}   News from Version 3:@{ub}
       - Support the final mSQL2 protocol.

@{b}   News from Version 2:@{ub}
       - Client code included into the library (no external program required
         any more).
       - Functions that don't require a "real" connection like @{"MsqlDataSeek()" Link "MsqlDataSeek()"}
         don't need a MsqlConnection argument anymore (this argument was
         needed with the previous version to exchange information with the
         external program).

@{b}   Requirement:@{ub}
       - A running TCP/IP stack (AmiTCP, Miami) to access distant DB server
         or mUSD to only access a local mSQL server.

@{b}   Note:@{ub}
       - the ixemul.library is not used any more.
       - Since new Times functions used static string in the original api,
         the library keeps buffers for each process that open the library.
         So, DON'T share the library base between process!

@{b}    A large parts of this documentation comes from the original msql api@{ub}
@{b}    documentation which is ©1998 Hughes Technologies Pty Ltd.@{ub}

@{b}   msql.library is (C) Copyright 1999 Christophe Sollet, All rights Reserved@{ub}
@EndNode

